.TH "pci_p2pmem_publish" 9 "pci_p2pmem_publish" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pci_p2pmem_publish \- publish the peer-to-peer DMA memory for use by other devices with pci_p2pmem_find()
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" pci_p2pmem_publish
.BI "(struct pci_dev *pdev "  ","
.BI "bool publish "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pdev" 12
the device with peer-to-peer DMA memory to publish
.IP "publish" 12
set to true to publish the memory, false to unpublish it
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Published memory can be used by other PCI device drivers for
peer-2-peer DMA operations. Non-published memory is reserved for
exclusive use of the device driver that registers the peer-to-peer
memory.
